    "Commentary Vol. 50": "These be the words which Moses `[char_Moses_Exo_2]` spake unto all Israel, etc.] Not\nwhat are related in the latter part of the preceding book, but what follow in\nthis; and which were spoken by him, not to the whole body of the people\ngathered together to hear him, which they could not do without a miracle;\nbut to the heads of the people, the representatives of them, who were\nconvened to hear what he had to say, in order to communicate it to the\npeople; unless we can suppose that Moses `[char_Moses_Exo_2]` at different times to several\nparties of them delivered the same things, until they had all heard them:\n1. Dissert. 7. sect. 14. p. 195, 196.\nft503 --  See Bochart. Hierozoic. par. 2. l. 4. c. 27. col. 622, 623.\nft504 --  Nat. Hist. l. 17. c. 28.\nft505 --  \u00c6l wyhy alw \u201cet non erunt tibi\u201d, Pagninus, Montanus.\nft506 --  De Termino Vitae, l. 3. sect. 3. p. 128.\nft507 --  \u201c----In ultimos orbis Britannos\u201d, Horat. Carmin. l.\n1. Dissert. 7. sect. 6. p. 186.)\nft526 --  Itinerar. p. 41-53.\nft527 --  Travels, sect. 3. p.\n1. Seder Olam Rabba, c. 10. p."
